<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 1255/1999 of 17 May 1999 on the common organisation of the market in milk and milk products(1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1670/2000(2), and in particular Article 15 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 17. mai 1999. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 1255/1999 piima- ja piimatooteturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1670/2000, (2) eriti selle artiklit 15, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2191/81(3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1207/98(4), provides for the grant of aid for the purchase of butter by non-profit-making institutions and organisations. In view of the current situation on the butter market and the level of sales under that Regulation, the aid amount must be reduced. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 2191/81, (3) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1207/98, (4) on s&auml;testatud v&otilde;i ostmiseks toetuse andmine mittetulundus&uuml;hingutele ja -liitudele; pidades silmas praegust olukorda v&otilde;iturul ja nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud m&uuml;&uuml;gi mahtu, tuleks abisummat v&auml;hendada; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) The measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Milk and Milk Products, </inglise>
